 Marten and Gordon were arrested in Brighton this Monday after the pair fled seven weeks ago with their newborn. The remains of the infant were discovered on Wednesday and police have revealed that the baby may have “been dead for several weeks”.    Now, on the street corner just yards away from where the remains were found, members of the public have gathered to pay tribute to the tragic passing. Many have placed flowers, but one mystery resident left a teddy bear along with a harrowing note, expressing wishes they could have helped the infant. The anonymous note attached to the white teddy said: “RIP little darling. “Am so traumatised. I should have followed your cries. I will never forget.”    We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express ‌ 